FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,FThe barrister had "red eyes", was
OL,7,Fslurring his speech, and smelled
OL,8,Fstrongly of alcohol when he arrived
OL,9,Ffor a hearing on March 13. He ended up
OL,10,Fbeing taken to hospital following the
OL,11,Fincident.
OL,13,FThe Bar Standards Board said in a
OL,14,Fmisconduct ruling that the lawyer was
OL,15,F"incapable of representing his
OL,16,Fclient", and fined him #1,000.
OL,26,@nD@SOUnD@\O]wD@AOUxD@GO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,FIn mitigation, Mr Hankinson said the
OL,7,Fincident was "a one-off" after more
OL,8,Fthan a decade of working as a
OL,9,Fbarrister. He also reported himself to
OL,10,Fthe regulator four days after the
OL,11,Fincident.
OL,13,FIn the aftermath, he stopped working
OL,14,Ffor five months and submitted to
OL,15,Fregular tests to prove he had quit
OL,16,Fdrinking alcohol.
OL,26,@oD@NOUoD@XO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,FHis client's hearing had to be
OL,7,Fadjourned on the day of the incident,
OL,8,Fbut it was rescheduled with Mr
OL,9,FHankinson being replaced by a more
OL,10,Fsenior barrister.
OL,12,FA panel for the regulator ruled that
OL,13,FMr Hankinson's behaviour had been
OL,14,F"reckless".
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@JO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,F"James Hankinson, a self-employed
OL,7,Fbarrister, behaved in a way which is
OL,8,Flikely to diminish the trust and
OL,9,Fconfidence which the public places in
OL,10,Fhim or in the profession when, on 13
OL,11,FMarch 2025, he attended Maidstone
OL,12,FCombined Court while under the
OL,13,Finfluence of alcohol to the extent
OL,14,Fthat he was drunk, collapsed while at
OL,15,Fcourt, and was unable to continue
OL,16,Frepresenting his client that day", the
OL,17,Fruling set out.
OL,19,F"After Mr Hankinson collapsed, an
OL,20,Fambulance was called, and he was taken
OL,21,Fto hospital.
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@aO]{D@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,F"Due to these events, Mr Hankinson was
OL,7,Fincapable of representing his client
OL,8,Fat the hearing which was scheduled to
OL,9,Ftake place that day and the matter was
OL,10,Fadjourned.
OL,12,F"Mr Hankinson informed his chambers
OL,13,Fabout what had happened. Mr
OL,14,FHankinson's client also reported to
OL,15,Fhis chambers that they had noticed a
OL,16,Fstrong smell of alcohol from Mr
OL,17,FHankinson, he had exhibited red eyes,
OL,18,Fand he had slurred speech when they
OL,19,Fmet him at the court earlier in the
OL,20,Fday."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU|D@EO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777532747
OL,3,CBarrister fined after turning up drunk
OL,4,Cto represent client in court
OL,6,F"Mr Hankinson stated his deep regret
OL,7,Ffor what had happened and said that he
OL,8,Fwas incredibly ashamed of his
OL,9,Factions", the ruling continued.
OL,11,F"Mr Hankinson provided mitigation,
OL,12,Fproof of his abstinence from alcohol
OL,13,Fsince 13 March, and further set out
OL,14,Fthe steps being taken by him to
OL,15,Faddress his conduct.
OL,17,F"Mr Hankinson voluntarily ceased to
OL,18,Fcarry out professional work as a
OL,19,Fbarrister until suitable arrangements
OL,20,Fwere put in place with chambers for
OL,21,Fhis return to work."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@HO]sD@AOUyD@AOU}D@TO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
